<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb92f9066-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s1726"><num value="1726">§ 1726.</num><heading> Postage collected unlawfully</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Whoever, being a postmaster or other person authorized to receive the postage of mail matter, fraudulently demands or receives any rate of postage or gratuity or reward other than is provided by law for the postage of such mail matter, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than six months, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb92f9067-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645">June 25, 1948, ch. 645</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/784">62 Stat. 784</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/B">Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(B)</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2146">108 Stat. 2146</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb92f9068-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idb92f9069-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 330 (<ref href="/us/act/1909-03-04/ch321/s207">Mar. 4, 1909, ch. 321, § 207</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/35/1128">35 Stat. 1128</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Minor verbal changes were made.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idb92f906a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idb92f906b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/322">Pub. L. 103–322</ref> substituted “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $100”.</p>
</note>
